<kml xmlns="http://www.opengis.net/kml/2.2">
<Document>
<name>Blue Ridge Parkway</name>
<description><![CDATA[<h2>Blue Ridge Parkway</h2><p><i>Virginia / North Carolina, USA · BRP, Rockfish Gap VA to Cherokee NC</i></p><p><b>America's longest linear park: 755 km, no commercial trucks, no stoplights, max 72 km/h.</b></p><table style='font-family:sans-serif'><tr><td><b>Approx. length:</b></td><td>523 km (325 mi)</td></tr><tr><td><b>Drive time:</b></td><td>12+ hrs end-to-end; ideally 5–7 days</td></tr><tr><td><b>Best season:</b></td><td>April–October; foliage peak mid-October</td></tr><tr><td><b>Watch out for:</b></td><td>Deer, fog (especially in spring), motorcycles passing on blind curves, RVs at 30 km/h, occasional sections closed for repair</td></tr><tr><td><b>Track points:</b></td><td>845</td></tr></table><hr><p>469 miles, no commercial trucks, no stoplights, no billboards, max 45 mph. New Deal project begun 1935, completed in 1987 with the Linn Cove Viaduct around Grandfather Mountain. The most-visited unit in the National Park System most years. Drive any 80 km section and you've seen something extraordinary; drive all 755 and you've watched the Appalachians shift from Virginia farmland in the north to Carolina balsam fir at over 1,800 m in the south. Mileposts count from MP 0 at Rockfish Gap (north) to MP 469 at the Smokies.</p><h3>Scenic points marked on this route:</h3><ul><li><b>Peaks of Otter</b> — Trio of summits with 1960s lodge and Abbott Lake. Hike Sharp Top (2.5 km, steep) for one of the BRP's best 360° views.</li><li><b>Mabry Mill</b> — Most-photographed spot on the parkway — a working 1910 grist mill with reflected millpond. Demonstrations summer weekends.</li><li><b>Linn Cove Viaduct</b> — Last section completed (1987). 379 m segmental concrete viaduct curving around Grandfather Mountain — built without disturbing the slope beneath.</li><li><b>Linville Falls</b> — 27 m falls dropping into Linville Gorge, 'the Grand Canyon of the Southern Appalachians.' Multiple viewpoints.</li><li><b>Craggy Gardens</b> — Catawba rhododendron tunnel — peaks mid-June. Short trail to a 1,738 m bald with continuous panoramas.</li><li><b>Richland Balsam</b> — Highest point on the parkway (1,845 m). Spruce-fir forest like southern Canada; a reminder of the last Ice Age.</li></ul><hr><p><i>Track geometry is interpolated between named waypoints — use a routing service to snap to actual road for navigation. Waypoints, scenic POIs, and notes are reliable.</i></p>]]></description>
