<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Peaks of Otter</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Trio of summits with 1960s lodge and Abbott Lake. Hike Sharp Top (2.5 km, steep) for one of the BRP's best 360° views.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-79.600500,37.449500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Mabry Mill</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Most-photographed spot on the parkway — a working 1910 grist mill with reflected millpond. Demonstrations summer weekends.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-80.408000,36.748000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Linn Cove Viaduct</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Last section completed (1987). 379 m segmental concrete viaduct curving around Grandfather Mountain — built without disturbing the slope beneath.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-81.819000,36.095000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Linville Falls</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[27 m falls dropping into Linville Gorge, 'the Grand Canyon of the Southern Appalachians.' Multiple viewpoints.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-81.927500,35.952800,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Craggy Gardens</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Catawba rhododendron tunnel — peaks mid-June. Short trail to a 1,738 m bald with continuous panoramas.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-82.382900,35.700000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Richland Balsam</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Highest point on the parkway (1,845 m). Spruce-fir forest like southern Canada; a reminder of the last Ice Age.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-82.988600,35.362000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
